.TH DNS-UPDATE 1 "April 27, 2026" "dns-update" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dns-update \- keep DNS A and AAAA records aligned with egress IP addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dns-update
[\fB\--version\fR]
[\fB\-config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-delete\fR[=\fIa|aaaa|both\fR]]
[\fB\-dry-run\fR]
[\fB\-force-push\fR]
[\fB\-validate-config\fR]
[\fB\-print-effective-config\fR]
[\fB\-timeout\fR \fIDURATION\fR]
[\fB\-verbose\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dns-update
probes the current IPv4 and IPv6 egress addresses of the local host and updates
the configured DNS A and AAAA records when the observed addresses differ from
the current provider state. With
.B \-force-push,
matching records are refreshed anyway so the provider receives an update even
when the observed IPs have not changed.
.B \-delete
switches the program into an explicit delete mode that skips egress probing and
removes managed
.B A
and/or
.B AAAA
records for the configured name. Bare
.B \-delete
deletes both families; use
.BR \-delete=a ,
.BR \-delete=aaaa ,
or
.BR \-delete=both
for explicit selection. Delete mode is compatible with
.BR \-dry-run
and mutually exclusive with
.BR \-force-push .
.P
The program is intended for timer-driven operation, including systemd timer
deployments on Linux, launchd jobs on macOS, and Task Scheduler jobs on
Windows. It supports dry-run execution, bounded retries, and provider
reconciliation against the live DNS record state before applying changes.
.P
Each probe response must parse as
.B ip=<address>
or
.BR ip=none .
Probe failures abort reconciliation; only explicit
.B ip=none
suppresses a managed address family.
.P
The provider-offline introspection modes,
.BR \-validate-config
and
.BR \-print-effective-config ,
still load and validate the assembled configuration, including the configured
Cloudflare token-file path, before exiting. They stop before provider
initialization and do not contact Cloudflare.
.P
In the packaged systemd deployment, the Cloudflare token source file is stored
at
.I /etc/dns-update/cloudflare.token
and is materialized into the service credential directory by
.BR LoadCredential= .
The configured token path must resolve to a regular file without symlinked
deeper path components.
Published packages intentionally avoid self-unpacking binary compression so the
installed binary remains compatible with the hardened systemd unit.
.P
Published releases also include macOS and Windows archives. Those platforms use
native schedulers instead of systemd: launchd on macOS and Task Scheduler on
Windows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \--version
Print the binary version to standard output and exit without loading
configuration or contacting a provider.
.TP
.B \-config
Load configuration from the specified JSON file. If omitted and
.B DNS_UPDATE_CONFIG
is unset, the program first looks for
.I config.json
in the current working directory and then
.I /etc/dns-update/config.json .
.TP
.B \-dry-run
Print the changes that would be made without mutating DNS records.
.TP
.B \-delete
Delete managed address records instead of reconciling to observed egress IPs.
Bare
.B \-delete
deletes both
.B A
and
.B AAAA
records. Use
.BR \-delete=a ,
.BR \-delete=aaaa ,
or
.BR \-delete=both
to select the affected record families. This option is mutually exclusive with
.BR \-force-push .
.TP
.B \-force-push
Refresh matching A and AAAA records even when the observed egress IPs already
match the provider state. The desired target remains the observed IPs, so this
flag forces a provider write without changing what the tool considers current.
.TP
.B \-validate-config
Load and validate the assembled configuration, including the configured
Cloudflare token-file path; print
.B config is valid
to standard output, and exit before provider initialization or Cloudflare
network calls. This option is mutually exclusive with
.BR \-print-effective-config .
.TP
.B \-print-effective-config
Load and validate the assembled configuration, including the configured
Cloudflare token-file path; print the fully assembled effective configuration
as JSON and exit before provider initialization or Cloudflare network calls.
This option is mutually exclusive with
.BR \-validate-config .
.TP
.B \-timeout
Apply a global timeout to one reconciliation cycle, including retries and
backoff. A value of
.B 0
disables the global timeout.
.TP
.B \-verbose
Enable debug logging.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_CONFIG
Path to the JSON configuration file. This has the same effect as
.BR \-config .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_DRY_RUN
Boolean override for
.BR \-dry-run .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_VERBOSE
Boolean override for
.BR \-verbose .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_TIMEOUT
Duration override for
.BR \-timeout .
.TP
.B DNS_UPDATE_PROVIDER_CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_FILE
Override only the configured Cloudflare token-file path. This is primarily used
by the packaged systemd service to point the binary at a systemd-managed
credential file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ./config.json
Implicit first config lookup path when neither
.BR \-config
nor
.B DNS_UPDATE_CONFIG
is set.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/config.json
Fallback JSON configuration file for packaged and systemd deployments.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/config.example.json
Shipped sample configuration for packaged deployments.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/cloudflare.token
Source file for the Cloudflare API token used by packaged systemd deployments.
.TP
.I /etc/dns-update/dns-update.env
Optional environment overrides for packaged systemd deployments.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Configuration load or validation failed, provider initialization failed, or the
reconciliation run failed.
.TP
.B 2
Command-line usage or flag parsing failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd (1),
.BR systemd.timer (5)
